00:56.224 --> 00:58.351
Who's gonna do the dishes
for the next week?

00:58.434 --> 01:03.231
Boys versus girls.
Testosterone versus estrogen.

01:03.314 --> 01:06.442
- Standing up to pee versus the squat-
- Phil, come on!

01:11.197 --> 01:14.409
Swing and a miss.
He's in her head, Luke.

01:14.492 --> 01:16.619
And boys rule and girls drool.

01:16.703 --> 01:19.831
You drool all the time.
Mom had to take you to a specialist.

01:19.914 --> 01:22.208
I'm still growing
into my tongue.

01:22.292 --> 01:23.835
Hey, Mom, can I go
to the movies with Robin?

01:23.918 --> 01:26.212
No, you may not,
'cause you are still grounded.

01:26.296 --> 01:28.298
Then can I be sent to my room?

01:28.381 --> 01:30.425
No, 'cause we're having
some fun family time.

01:30.508 --> 01:32.927
We're gonna spend this
beautiful afternoon outside...

01:33.011 --> 01:35.346
in the fresh air
getting some exercise, okay?

01:35.430 --> 01:36.848
Pitch it, Phil.

01:44.272 --> 01:45.773
- Oh, well.
- That's the game.

01:45.857 --> 01:47.233
What do you mean?
We just started.

01:47.317 --> 01:49.110
That was our only ball.

01:49.193 --> 01:52.405
So what? The game's over just because
you're afraid of stupid Mr. Kleezak?

01:52.488 --> 01:54.991
Yep. I'm not going over there.
That was fun.

01:55.074 --> 01:58.244
If Hannibal Lecter and Freddy
Krueger had a love child,

01:58.328 --> 02:00.538
he would be afraid
of our next door neighbor.

02:00.622 --> 02:02.665
I don't have a mean thing
to say about anyone,

02:02.749 --> 02:05.460
but Mr. Kleezak is...

02:05.543 --> 02:07.211
not a nice person.

02:07.295 --> 02:08.880
Easy,honey.

02:10.340 --> 02:12.258
[ Mitchell ] Hey, Haley.
Oh, hey, Uncle Mitchell.

02:12.342 --> 02:14.052
Hey, is your mom home?

02:14.135 --> 02:16.262
No. She had to take Alex
to the oncologist.

02:16.346 --> 02:18.890
- Oh, my God. What's wrong?
- She needed new glasses.

02:19.015 --> 02:21.643
Oh. Did you mean optometrist?
Whatever.

02:21.768 --> 02:23.561
So, should I give her a message?
Yes, yes.

02:23.645 --> 02:26.773
Could you ask her if she could possibly
babysit Lily on Saturday night?

02:26.856 --> 02:28.691
We'd really,
really appreciate it.

02:28.816 --> 02:31.444
Saturday night we're having dinner
with Pepper, Longines and Crispin.

02:31.569 --> 02:34.989
They're our gay friends.
I think that was clear.

02:35.073 --> 02:38.534
I've been spending a lot of time with
a lot of straight people lately,

02:38.618 --> 02:40.953
and, darlin',
I need a night with my homeys.

02:41.037 --> 02:43.164
You mean homos.
[ Giggles ]

02:43.247 --> 02:45.583
Yeah. You know what?
Maybe you should stay in and babysit.

02:47.043 --> 02:49.837
Yeah, our babysitter bailed,
and we're kind of in a bind so-

02:49.921 --> 02:51.506
I can do it.
I can watch Lily.

02:51.589 --> 02:53.591
I'm really good.
I'm babysitting Luke right now.

02:53.675 --> 02:56.969
Oh, yeah? You want-
You want to babysit Lily?

02:57.053 --> 02:58.888
[ Chuckling ]
Oh, that's very sweet, honey.

02:58.971 --> 03:01.099
But you're-
you're a very popular girl.

03:01.182 --> 03:02.975
I'm sure you have
better things to do, so-

03:03.059 --> 03:05.853
Seriously.
I'm totally free.

03:05.937 --> 03:08.690
Being grounded is so much worse
than it was in the olden days.

03:08.773 --> 03:11.067
My friends text and Facebook
all the fun stuff they're doing...

03:11.150 --> 03:14.237
while I'm stuck at home
playing Jenga with my dad.

03:14.320 --> 03:16.489
[Chuckling]

03:16.572 --> 03:18.157
Are you serious?

03:18.241 --> 03:21.411
You don't even have to pay me.
I promise I'll take super good care of her.

03:21.494 --> 03:23.955
Okay. Well, that would
be great. Thank you.

03:24.038 --> 03:26.332
Yes. Well, we'll see you on Saturday night.
Bye, sweetie.

03:26.457 --> 03:28.042
Bye.
[ Beeps ]

03:28.960 --> 03:31.295
Luke?

03:32.130 --> 03:33.881
Luke?

03:35.508 --> 03:39.303
What are you thinking?
Haley is a very sweet and fashionable girl,

03:39.387 --> 03:41.514
but seems hardly
a responsible caregiver.

03:41.639 --> 03:45.017
Well, you know what? We needed a sitter.
She's family. I say we give her a shot.

03:45.101 --> 03:47.478
A shot. Oh, with our only child.
Sure, why not?

03:47.562 --> 03:51.023
If something goes wrong, we'll just pop
over to the Orient, grab another one.

