04:01.743 --> 04:04.078
My name is Luke Dunphy.
I live next door.

04:04.162 --> 04:06.539
- What do you want?
- I wanna get our ball from your yard.

04:07.915 --> 04:11.794
I don't want you messing around back there.
Just go home.

04:11.878 --> 04:13.421
- Are you going scuba diving?
- Hmm?

04:13.504 --> 04:15.965
Why do you have that tank?

04:16.089 --> 04:19.010
You being smart?
You mean in school?

04:19.093 --> 04:20.636
Well, I do okay.

04:20.720 --> 04:22.722
My teacher says
I get distracted.

04:22.805 --> 04:25.641
- Why do you have that tube in your nose?
- For fun.

04:25.725 --> 04:27.852
Really? Can I try?

04:27.935 --> 04:32.231
- It's oxygen.
- We have that in our house, but we don't need tanks.

04:32.315 --> 04:34.692
Oh, for God's sake.
Just get your ball.

04:34.776 --> 04:36.027
Okay.

04:36.110 --> 04:37.904
[ Inhales Deeply]

04:44.076 --> 04:46.621
Oh, my God.
I was watching the news,

04:46.704 --> 04:49.373
and another flock of birds
fell out of the sky.

04:49.457 --> 04:51.542
Dead.
What is happening?

04:51.626 --> 04:54.212
Sweetie, you gotta stop
watching the news.

04:54.295 --> 04:57.507
That's your big solution?
Embrace ignorance?

04:57.590 --> 05:00.259
What are you two arguing about?
Never mind. I don't wanna know.

05:00.343 --> 05:02.637
- Oh.
- Be back in a couple hours.

05:02.720 --> 05:04.222
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Where are you going?

05:04.305 --> 05:06.474
To my friend Walt's house
to watch High Noon.

05:06.557 --> 05:08.893
Ooh, I love Westerns.
The bloodier the better.

05:08.976 --> 05:10.478
That's my favorite type
of movie.

05:10.561 --> 05:13.397
That and anything set against the
backdrop of competitive cheerleading.

05:13.481 --> 05:15.775
Is Walt the one
who's always skateboarding?

05:15.858 --> 05:17.860
No. Where would he
put his oxygen tank?

05:17.944 --> 05:19.779
Okay. Now I'm really confused.

05:19.862 --> 05:23.407
[Chuckling ] You sound like Walt.
He gets confused a lot. it's hilarious.

05:23.491 --> 05:25.368
Wait. Are we talking about
Mr. Kleezak?

05:25.451 --> 05:29.914
Yeah. I went over to his house to get
my ball, and we've been hanging out.

05:29.997 --> 05:32.124
You were in
Mr. Kleezak's house?

05:32.250 --> 05:34.627
Luke, that is not okay.
Why not?

05:34.710 --> 05:36.796
He's really nice.
And funny.

05:36.879 --> 05:39.924
Listen to this joke. Okay.
Two crabs walk into a bar-

05:40.049 --> 05:42.176
Phil, this is not good.
Honey, don't jump to conclusions.

05:42.260 --> 05:44.762
- Let him finish the joke.
- And one of them has a limp.

05:44.887 --> 05:48.099
Uh-huh. You may not go
back to that man's house.

05:48.182 --> 05:50.643
- Why not?
- Because he's weird.

05:50.768 --> 05:52.228
And not very nice.
Yeah.

05:52.353 --> 05:54.689
That's what you said about
my friend Oliver. Oliver.

05:54.772 --> 05:56.482
The Oliver who almost
burned down our garage?

05:56.566 --> 05:59.861
He likes to melt stuff!
Like you're so perfect.

05:59.944 --> 06:02.822
Luke, I'm sorry, but your mother and
I just aren't comfortable with this.

06:02.905 --> 06:06.492
That's so unfair! You don't even know him
'cause you're too afraid to talk to him.

06:06.576 --> 06:08.202
Buddy, we're just
looking out for you.

06:08.286 --> 06:10.955
You never like
any of my friends!

06:11.706 --> 06:13.791
[Sighs]

06:13.916 --> 06:16.085
We're doing the right thing.
Absolutely.

06:17.753 --> 06:19.881
- Aren't we?
- I don't know.

06:19.964 --> 06:22.133
I mean, he makes a point.
We don't know the man.

06:22.216 --> 06:25.177
And little kids can be friends
with old people, right?

06:25.261 --> 06:27.096
Of course they can.
There's tons of examples.

06:27.179 --> 06:30.141
Up, um, Gran Torino,
True Grit.

06:30.224 --> 06:32.810
Cartoon, kills himself,
she loses an arm.

06:32.894 --> 06:34.770
- We've gotta go talk to that guy.
- Now?

06:34.896 --> 06:37.189
Yeah.
It's so dark.

06:38.316 --> 06:40.443
Okay. So the numbers
are by the phone.

06:40.526 --> 06:42.486
There's food in the fridge.
I just changed her diaper.

06:42.570 --> 06:45.114
So all you need to do is put
her down in about half hour...

06:45.197 --> 06:47.116
and not let a serial killer
in the front door.

06:47.199 --> 06:50.077
- Well, what if he's cute?
- Well, then save him for us.

06:50.161 --> 06:51.287
[ Laughing]

06:51.370 --> 06:53.247
Nobody in, nobody out.
No.

06:53.331 --> 06:56.584
Oh, we're gonna be totally fine.
You just go, get your gay on.

06:56.667 --> 06:59.295
Oh, it is on
like Donkey Kong.

06:59.378 --> 07:01.380
Or clearly it's not on yet.
But it will be.

07:01.464 --> 07:03.174
So,okay.
Come on. Let's go.

07:03.257 --> 07:06.719
I'm telling you, kid, this is a
concert you're never gonna forget.

07:06.802 --> 07:08.721
Greatest music in the world.

07:10.014 --> 07:11.474
Wait a minute.
What's this?

07:11.599 --> 07:14.268
What do you mean?
What are we seeing?

07:14.352 --> 07:16.103
The symphony.
The Four Seasons.

07:16.187 --> 07:18.105
I thought we were seeing
Frankie Valli & the 4 Seasons.

07:18.189 --> 07:20.566
- No. it's Vivaldi.
- Oh, crap.

07:20.650 --> 07:22.610
You mean nothing but instruments?
I'm outta here.

07:22.693 --> 07:25.446
- No, you're not out. You're in.
- I hate this kind of music.

07:25.571 --> 07:29.492
Jay, you always do that. Every time we try
something new, your first reaction is always no.

07:29.575 --> 07:31.702
I'm old enough to know what I
like and what I don't like.

07:31.786 --> 07:33.621
- What about the crab cakes?
- That was a fluke.

07:33.704 --> 07:37.041
And I can't slather that
boring music in tartar sauce.

07:37.124 --> 07:41.879
So I have to try new things- like
scrambled eggs- but you don't have to?

07:41.963 --> 07:44.632
You see what you're doing?
You're tearing this family apart!

07:44.715 --> 07:47.802
Take it down a notch.
You two go in, have a great time.

07:47.885 --> 07:49.929
- I'll see you later.
- What are you going to do?

07:50.012 --> 07:53.307
I'm gonna walk like a man, fast
as I can, to that bar over there.

07:53.391 --> 07:56.018
And if you knew Frankie Valli,
you'd be cracking up right now.

07:57.770 --> 07:59.605
It's okay.

07:59.689 --> 08:02.441
[ Chattering ]

08:02.525 --> 08:03.985
John Schneider was the one.

08:04.110 --> 08:06.529
John Schneider from Dukes of Hazzard?
That was your first crush?

08:06.612 --> 08:09.657
Oh, my God, yes.
Bo Duke. Delicious.

08:09.740 --> 08:12.910
He was a redneck who drove a car
called the General Lee...

08:12.994 --> 08:14.870
with a giant
Confederate flag on it.

08:14.954 --> 08:16.956
That wasn't
a turn off for you?

08:17.039 --> 08:19.667
I know he was all kinds of wrong, but
the heart wants what the heart wants.

08:19.750 --> 08:22.253
Richard Gere.
Oh, my God.

08:22.336 --> 08:25.006
I'll be the officer-
don't be a gentleman.

08:25.131 --> 08:28.384
Montgomery Clift.
Who?

08:28.467 --> 08:30.177
Don't do that, Crispin.
You're not that young.

08:30.261 --> 08:33.097
Anyway, my crush was gay.
At least I had a shot.

08:33.179 --> 08:34.890
You had a shot with Montgomery Clift?
How old are you?

08:34.974 --> 08:36.892
[All Laughing]

08:36.976 --> 08:40.479
I will cut you like
it was nothing, farm boy.

08:40.563 --> 08:42.356
Oh. See, I miss this.

08:42.481 --> 08:44.191
Wait. What about you, Mitchell?
Um, okay.

08:44.275 --> 08:46.902
I didn't know it was a crush because
I was only eight at the time.

08:47.028 --> 08:50.072
I knew when I was eight.
Everyone knew when you were eight.

08:50.156 --> 08:51.782
Longines, get up.
We're switching seats.

08:51.866 --> 08:53.409
[All Laughing]

08:53.492 --> 08:55.619
Okay. Okay. Back to me.
Back to me. Back to me.

08:55.703 --> 08:58.164
So I had just seen
St. Elmo's Fire.

08:58.247 --> 09:00.708
Oh, Mitchell, look.
It's your father.

09:00.791 --> 09:02.960
[ Pepper]
Oh, that's your father?

09:03.044 --> 09:06.172
- He's cute.
- Okay. Can you please turn it off for one second?

09:06.255 --> 09:07.840
Oh, he's all alone.
Invite him over.

09:07.923 --> 09:09.717
Yeah, that's not something
we're gonna do.

09:09.800 --> 09:11.594
Relax. Your dad
knows you're gay.

09:11.677 --> 09:14.722
- He doesn't know I'm this gay.
- Excuse us?

09:14.805 --> 09:18.017
- Oh, Mr. Pritchett! Yoo-hoo!
- Jay. Jay.

09:18.100 --> 09:20.811
[ Longines] Oh, he looks like that
dentist you hooked up with in Laguna.

09:20.895 --> 09:23.230
Oh, yeah, yeah.
That was in my daddy phase.

09:23.314 --> 09:25.399
Yes, please, keep this up.
This is fun for me.

09:25.524 --> 09:27.234
Fellas, how you doin'?
Hey,Dad.

09:27.359 --> 09:29.528
[ Cameron ] Hi, Jay.
Hello, Daddy.

09:29.653 --> 09:33.032
What are you doing here? I'm just getting a
drink while Gloria and Manny see a show.

09:33.115 --> 09:35.284
- Well, please, join us.
- No, I don't want to intrude.

09:35.367 --> 09:37.411
- He doesn't want to intrude.
- You are not intruding.

09:37.536 --> 09:39.663
I'm gonna watch the game.
He wants to watch the game.

09:39.747 --> 09:41.957
Ch, sit down.
We're up by 25 with a minute to go.

09:42.041 --> 09:44.502
Uh, maybe just
for a minute. Okay.

09:55.346 --> 09:59.308
So what does a guy gotta do to get a
drink around here? Nobody say anything.

09:59.391 --> 10:01.185
[All Laughing]

10:01.268 --> 10:03.729
Justin, more booze.

10:03.813 --> 10:06.941
Mitchell was just about to tell
us who his first boy crush was.

10:07.066 --> 10:09.068
No, I wasn't.
Let me bring you up to speed.

10:09.151 --> 10:12.404
Crispin's was Joey Mclntyre-
whoever that is.

10:12.488 --> 10:14.532
Longines said John Schneider.

10:14.615 --> 10:18.077
- Your name is Longines?
- I know. I never stood a chance.

10:18.160 --> 10:20.746
Cam's was Richard Gere.
And I was Monty Clift.

10:20.830 --> 10:23.082
Well, at least yours was gay.
I mean, you might've had a shot.

10:23.165 --> 10:24.959
Thank you!

10:25.042 --> 10:27.503
Crispin, up.
I'm sitting next to this one.

10:27.586 --> 10:29.588
[All churning]

10:29.672 --> 10:31.173
[ Pepper]
Welcome.

10:32.716 --> 10:34.885
He's right there.
All right.

10:40.975 --> 10:43.686
Mr. Kleezak? Mr.
Kleezak? It's open.

10:43.769 --> 10:46.355
Honey, he's not moving.
ls he okay?

10:46.438 --> 10:50.067
Well, there's only one way
to find out.

10:54.321 --> 10:56.073
[Grunts]

10:58.409 --> 10:59.910
[Whispering ]
Mr. Kleezak?

11:01.912 --> 11:03.831
Mr. Kleezak?
Okay.

11:03.914 --> 11:05.791
I- I don't know
if he's breathing.

11:05.916 --> 11:09.003
Does he have a pulse?
Well, there's only one way to find out.

11:09.086 --> 11:11.297
Will you stop pushing me?
You do it.

11:11.380 --> 11:14.675
I hate this.
I'm gonna kill Luke.

11:18.387 --> 11:19.847
Oh, my God.
He's ice cold.

11:19.930 --> 11:22.391
- Hey. - [ Screams ] Oh, my God!

11:22.474 --> 11:24.768
- [ Phil Groans]
- [Claire] I'm sorry.

11:24.894 --> 11:27.188
- We thought there was something wrong with you.
- Sorry.

11:27.313 --> 11:29.982
What? We thought there was
something wrong with you.

11:30.065 --> 11:32.776
- Phil.
- Hi.

11:32.860 --> 11:35.738
We haven't, uh, formally met.
Phil Dunphy.

11:35.821 --> 11:39.241
Yeah, I know you. You're the guy who
just broke into my house and fondled me.

11:39.325 --> 11:43.329
No. We were just concerned that
you looked dead. No offense.

11:43.412 --> 11:45.623
What- What-
What are you doing here?

11:45.706 --> 11:50.085
Oh, um, our son, Luke, told us that you
invited him over here to watch movies.

11:50.169 --> 11:54.423
And I'm sure you could understand why
we would be concerned about that.

11:54.506 --> 11:56.300
- No.
- Phil.

11:56.425 --> 11:58.427
You're doing great.
Honey-

11:58.510 --> 12:00.638
what, are you saying that
I'm some kind of pervert?

12:00.763 --> 12:02.848
No!
Probably not.

12:02.932 --> 12:04.808
Look, I didn't ask him
to come over here.

12:04.892 --> 12:08.187
I was minding my own business,
like you should be.

12:08.270 --> 12:09.271
Okay.

12:09.355 --> 12:12.483
But in all fairness,
our son is our business.

12:12.566 --> 12:14.318
Well, then keep him.

12:14.443 --> 12:19.073
And keep your daughter from
driving into my garbage cans. Uh-

12:19.156 --> 12:23.077
And keep your blinds closed when
you're doing your little sexy dance.

12:23.160 --> 12:26.163
Oh, God.
He's seen my sexy dance.

12:31.335 --> 12:34.922
So I'm 12 years old. I'm staying
overnight at my best friend Jim's house.

12:35.047 --> 12:37.883
Neither of us want to go to sleep.
I know where this is going.

12:37.967 --> 12:40.386
- You're better than that, Crispin.
- [All Chuckling]

12:41.262 --> 12:42.721
So we sneak off
to the movies,

12:42.805 --> 12:46.350
and we see this little picture
called Solomon and Sheba.

12:46.433 --> 12:49.270
- And Sheba was-
- [ Together] Gina Lollobrigida!

12:49.353 --> 12:52.481
Bingo! And for the rest of my life, I swore
one day I would marry Gina Lollobrigida.

12:52.564 --> 12:55.401
- Well, Dad, you kinda did.
- I hear that!

12:55.484 --> 12:57.194
[All Laughing]
Mmm.

12:57.278 --> 12:58.821
These are good.
What's in 'em'?

12:58.904 --> 13:00.614
It's a margarita
with a shot of absinthe.

13:00.698 --> 13:02.741
Absinthe makes the heart
grow fonder.

13:02.825 --> 13:05.494
Ah, are you making a bad pun
or just lisping?

13:05.577 --> 13:08.914
I can't believe I drove all the
way to the Valley to pick you up.

13:09.873 --> 13:11.917
Justin, more booze!

13:12.001 --> 13:14.253
Oh!

13:14.336 --> 13:17.131
[ Cameron ] Haley! Hi.
Is everything okay?

13:17.214 --> 13:20.634
- Yeah. Why?
- Because I just saw a man walk through the living room.

13:20.718 --> 13:23.470
What?
Where are you?

13:23.554 --> 13:25.514
I can see through the camera
on the computer.

13:25.597 --> 13:27.975
You're spying on me?
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

13:28.058 --> 13:29.810
That is so lame.

13:29.893 --> 13:34.106
Look, I don't know what you think you
saw- maybe the TV or the reflection.

13:34.231 --> 13:37.943
Or maybe you think that my body is just shaped
like a boy, like I don't have hips or something.

13:38.027 --> 13:40.279
No,no,no,no.
You have a darling figure.

13:40.362 --> 13:44.199
- I was just concerned that-
- That hurts so much.

13:44.283 --> 13:48.037
This is the kind of thing that I expect
from my mother, but not from my cool uncle.

13:48.120 --> 13:52.458
- So, thank you for all of your trust.
- Okay, um, sorry. Sorry.

13:52.541 --> 13:53.834
[Beeps]

13:53.917 --> 13:56.420
[ Sighs ]
Unbelievable.

13:56.545 --> 13:59.840
You gotta go.
Okay.

13:59.923 --> 14:04.928
♪♪ [All Humming, Scatting]

14:10.434 --> 14:11.935
Yeah!
All right.

14:12.019 --> 14:14.021
Thank you.

14:14.104 --> 14:16.815
[ Chuckling ] Dad, I've
never seen you sing before.

14:16.899 --> 14:19.651
Well, you never saw me in the shower.
And don't anybody go there.

14:21.153 --> 14:24.698
When I was 12 years old, my
father walked into my bedroom...

14:24.782 --> 14:29.703
and caught me doing the most
embarrassing thing that a boy can do-

14:29.787 --> 14:31.872
dancing to Madonna's
“Lucky Star.”

14:31.955 --> 14:36.794
And from that moment on, there's always
been a part of me that I've kept from him.

14:36.877 --> 14:39.755
And yet here he was
laughing with my friends.

14:39.838 --> 14:44.676
And- I don't know-
maybe the problem was me.

14:44.760 --> 14:46.804
[All Laughing]

14:46.887 --> 14:48.472
- Rob Lowe! - [ Together] Where?

14:48.555 --> 14:51.183
No. Rob Lowe from St. Elmo's Fire.
That was- That was my crush.

14:51.266 --> 14:54.311
- I loved him.
- I get that. He's a good-looking kid.

14:54.395 --> 14:56.063
Mm-hmm.
Right?

14:56.146 --> 14:58.273
Yeah.
Hey, “Walk Like a Man.”

14:58.399 --> 15:01.110
Well, I can sing it, but I can't do it.
[All Laugh ]

15:01.193 --> 15:04.279
♪♪ [ Vocalizing ]

15:04.363 --> 15:07.241
I think I just pulled something.

15:07.324 --> 15:09.785
Nurse!

15:11.870 --> 15:14.498
[ Phone Ringing]

15:18.210 --> 15:20.796
- Hello?
- Please tell me that you have my shoes.

15:20.879 --> 15:22.673
Why would I have your shoes?

15:22.756 --> 15:24.800
Because I left them at your
uncles's house last night.

15:24.883 --> 15:27.177
What? How could you leave
without your shoes?

15:27.261 --> 15:29.721
I go a lot of places
without shoes.

15:29.805 --> 15:31.723
I'm not wearing shoes right now.

15:31.807 --> 15:35.310
Oh, wait. That's 'cause I left
them at your uncles's house.

15:35.394 --> 15:37.771
This is a disaster!

15:37.855 --> 15:39.648
Maybe they'll think
they're theirs.

15:39.731 --> 15:42.359
They're gay.
They know what shoes they own.

15:44.903 --> 15:46.363
Thanks a lot, Walt.

15:46.447 --> 15:48.615
You couldn't be nice to
my parents for two seconds,

15:48.699 --> 15:50.617
so now I'm not allowed
to hang out with you.

15:50.701 --> 15:53.787
- What do you want from me?
- I thought you were my friend.

15:53.871 --> 15:56.081
You promised to teach me
how to grow tomatoes.

15:56.165 --> 15:58.125
And you were gonna take me
for an egg cream.

15:58.208 --> 16:00.461
Forget it.
You're a little kid.

16:00.544 --> 16:02.713
I don't need
the aggravation.

16:02.796 --> 16:05.007
Oh. Sorry I “aggravated” you.

16:05.090 --> 16:08.135
And just so you know, a lot
of people think I'm adorable.

16:16.268 --> 16:17.769
I can't open this.

16:17.853 --> 16:20.481
Maybe if you had gone
to the concert instead-

16:20.564 --> 16:23.150
- Could you open it, please?
- I would.

16:23.233 --> 16:26.570
But I'm old enough to know that I
don't like opening aspirin bottles.

16:26.653 --> 16:28.697
[Ringing]

16:28.780 --> 16:31.033
- Hello.
- Hey, Dad!

16:31.116 --> 16:33.702
How do you guys do it?
I thought cops could drink.

16:33.785 --> 16:35.454
[ Chuckles ]
Listen, I just-

16:35.537 --> 16:38.999
I wanted to say, I had such a good time
with you last night, and I wanted to-

16:39.082 --> 16:41.001
Hold on. I got call waiting!
Yeah.

16:41.084 --> 16:42.753
[Beeps]
Yeah?

16:42.836 --> 16:46.465
Woof. Not a morning person.
Good to know.

16:46.548 --> 16:50.636
Listen, I'm five away. I hope you like
blueberry scones and Dusty Springfield.

16:50.719 --> 16:52.721
Who is this?
Pepper, silly.

16:52.804 --> 16:56.558
It's gonna be a scorcher in the
desert today, so dress accordingly.

16:56.642 --> 16:58.727
Oh, this is your street.
See you in a minute.

17:00.354 --> 17:02.105
[ Beeps ]
Holy crap!

17:02.189 --> 17:05.358
That friend of yours, that Pepper-
he's on his way over here. Why?

17:05.442 --> 17:07.528
Well, you made a date with him last night.
Don't you remember?

17:07.611 --> 17:09.820
I think I would remember
if I made a date with a guy!

17:09.905 --> 17:12.074
I'm telling you,
I know a guy in Palm Springs...

17:12.156 --> 17:14.867
who has every single
vintage record known to man.

17:14.952 --> 17:17.329
I'm driving out there tomorrow.
Come with me!

17:17.412 --> 17:21.250
- It's a date!
- [ Together ] Yay!

17:21.333 --> 17:25.087
I was drunk! I'm not going shopping
with Priscilla, Queen of the Desert.

17:25.170 --> 17:27.881
Okay, Dad. Well, I'm feeling really
good about our relationship,

17:27.964 --> 17:30.175
and I wanna hold onto that
for a little while longer.

17:30.259 --> 17:33.679
So I'm gonna go ahead and hang up with you.
Give Pepper a big kiss for me.

17:36.098 --> 17:39.518
Gloria, now listen. I know that you're
upset with me about that concert thing,

17:39.601 --> 17:42.145
and rightfully so,
but you have to help me.

17:42.229 --> 17:45.857
- What is it?
- It seems I made plans with Mitchell's friend Pepper.

17:45.941 --> 17:47.609
That's someone's name?
Pepper?

17:47.693 --> 17:50.696
Yes. And that's just the tip of the iceberg.
There's another guy named Longines.

17:50.779 --> 17:52.656
But Pepper's gonna
be here any second.

17:52.739 --> 17:56.076
He's gonna take me to Palm Springs
to go shopping for records.

17:56.159 --> 17:59.413
Now, when he gets here, can you pretend
there's some kind of an emergency?

17:59.496 --> 18:01.039
Can you do that, please?

18:01.123 --> 18:05.252
Ay, Jay. I- I think you have to
take me now to the hospital.

18:05.335 --> 18:08.714
My head is in pain.

18:08.797 --> 18:10.924
- Do you mean like that?
- Yes. Thank you.

18:11.008 --> 18:12.801
[ Doorbell Rings ]
Okay. it's Showtime.

18:12.884 --> 18:15.387
And with this guy,
I mean that literally.

18:16.805 --> 18:18.807
I'm here!

18:18.890 --> 18:22.936
[ Chuckles ] Oh, my God!
What I could do with this house.

18:23.020 --> 18:25.564
Hello, Jay.

18:25.647 --> 18:27.149
Chop, chop.
It's a two-hour drive,

18:27.232 --> 18:29.109
not counting our stop
at the outlet mall.

18:29.192 --> 18:31.570
Okay. Uh-
Gloria, we're leaving!

18:31.653 --> 18:34.948
Hello. You must be Pepper.

18:35.032 --> 18:36.408
Ay an ay
My head.

18:36.491 --> 18:38.201
What's the matter, Gloria?

18:38.285 --> 18:40.537
Nothing.
I just had a little ice cream.

18:40.621 --> 18:43.749
- Huh?
- He hasn't stopped talking about you all day long.

18:43.832 --> 18:47.628
- Right.
- Wow. You are stunning.

18:47.711 --> 18:49.338
How rich are you?

18:49.421 --> 18:51.048
Are you sure
you're all right, Gloria?

18:51.131 --> 18:52.841
I feel great, mi amor

18:52.924 --> 18:54.926
I am so happy that
he's doing this with you...

18:55.010 --> 18:56.887
because I never get him
to do anything different.

18:56.970 --> 18:59.389
Like the Vivaldi.
Hmm.

18:59.514 --> 19:02.184
I think he likes you more than me.
[ Chuckles ]

19:02.267 --> 19:03.852
You two have
a great time together.

19:03.935 --> 19:05.479
All right, but we gotta
be back early,

19:05.604 --> 19:08.231
because, you know, I got that work thing.
No, no. I canceled everything.

19:08.315 --> 19:11.485
You don't have anything.
You can spend all day long with him.

19:11.568 --> 19:13.904
Wonderful.
Well, shall we?

19:15.947 --> 19:17.616
[ Dog Barking ]

19:17.699 --> 19:19.868
Oh, my God.
Tallulah!

19:19.951 --> 19:23.580
Oh! Don't worry. She'll stop
yapping when she gets on your lap.

19:25.040 --> 19:27.042
[ Barking Continues]

19:29.211 --> 19:31.588
Alex, honey, come on.
We're gonna be late.

19:32.673 --> 19:34.591
A herd of cows dropped dead
for no reason.

19:34.675 --> 19:36.343
I'm not going anywhere.

19:36.426 --> 19:38.720
Get your affairs in order, people.
This is the end.

19:38.804 --> 19:42.182
Don't be ridiculous.
There's nothing out there to be afraid of.

19:42.265 --> 19:43.517
Hey. Oh.
Oh.

19:43.600 --> 19:44.685
[ Claire ]
Mr. Kleezak.

19:44.768 --> 19:48.021
I'm not used to waking up
with people poking me.

19:48.105 --> 19:49.606
I was startled, you know.

19:49.690 --> 19:51.233
We are really sorry
about that.

19:51.316 --> 19:54.361
Yeah.
Well, these are onions.

19:54.444 --> 19:57.614
- From my garden.
- Wow. Thank you so much.

19:57.698 --> 19:59.199
That is so nice.

19:59.282 --> 20:02.661
Yeah. Well, don't go throwing any parades.
They're onions.

20:02.744 --> 20:04.621
[ Claire ] Uh-huh. Okay.

20:07.332 --> 20:10.168
I used to be a fireman,
you know.

20:10.252 --> 20:11.795
I don't hurt kids.

20:14.715 --> 20:16.591
Sir, would you like
to come in?

20:17.884 --> 20:20.887
Just tell the boy that Shane
is on today at 3:00.

20:21.012 --> 20:23.724
He should watch it.
Maybe you could tell him yourself.

20:23.807 --> 20:26.017
He- He's right upstairs. Hang on.
Luke, honey, come on down.

20:26.101 --> 20:28.645
Your friend Walt is here.

20:28.770 --> 20:30.731
This is just so sweet.
Yeah.

20:30.814 --> 20:33.442
Well, just don't
start dancing.

20:33.525 --> 20:35.068
[ Mitchell ]
People can surprise you.

20:35.152 --> 20:39.448
You get used to thinking of them
one way, stuck in their roles.

20:39.531 --> 20:41.616
They are what they are.

20:41.700 --> 20:43.785
And then they do something
that shows you...

20:43.869 --> 20:47.998
there's all this depth and dimension
that you never knew existed.

20:48.081 --> 20:49.708
Are you talking
about Rob Lowe?

20:49.791 --> 20:51.835
I'm just saying
he's a very versatile actor.

20:51.918 --> 20:54.546
I think his good looks
have actually held him back.

20:54.629 --> 20:57.007
Well, I can relate
to that.

21:00.177 --> 21:02.053
[ Doorbell Rings]

21:02.179 --> 21:04.097
Haley!
We need to talk.

21:04.181 --> 21:08.185
I know I freaked out on you last night, but
you have to see it from my point of view.

21:08.268 --> 21:10.020
- You were totally spying on me.
- I know.

21:10.103 --> 21:12.647
You were invading my
First Amendment right to privacy.

21:12.731 --> 21:13.815
We were.

21:13.899 --> 21:16.026
I'm sick and tired of people
not trusting me!

21:16.151 --> 21:18.028
I get it.
And especially you guys.

21:18.111 --> 21:21.323
I don't think of you guys as my uncles.
I think of you as my friends.

21:21.406 --> 21:24.242
And if your friends don't believe
in you, then what else do you have?

21:24.326 --> 21:27.245
- Dylan's shoes.
- Please don't tell my mom.

21:28.497 --> 21:30.373
Buckle up.

